name: Cape May Beaches
description: Visit these beautiful and expansive pearly white beaches with mouth-dropping views. Across the various beaches, vacationers can swim, skimboard, surf, fish, kayak and play volleyball in designated areas. Lifeguards are on duty and many enjoy swimming in the cool waters during summer. At sunset or sunrise, the beaches and waves provide a majestic scenery complement with dolphin sightings.

name: Washington Street Mall
description: The Washington Street Mall is one-stop shop for all your retail. Ranging from book stores, home goods stores, clothing stores and much more. There is beautiful buildings and pathways to explore, along with many restaurants and sweets being sold

name: Jersey Shore Alpacas
description: Interact with gentle and friendly alpacas at this calming and whimsical farm. This farm is home to 20 fluffy alpacas where patrons can interact with them and even purchase sweaters, gloves, and socks made from alpaca fleece.

name: Cape May Lighthouse
description: Built in 1859 and opened to the public in 1988, the Cape May Lighthouse challenges travelers to scale 199 steps to reach the top of the lighthouse. Waiting for them is a glorious and panoramic oceanfront view. The ones who prefer to remain on the ground can enjoy the Oil House, which contains a visitor center and a museum shop with souvenirs.

name: Emlen Physick Estate
description: Visit the Emlen Physick Estate, the only Victorian-era house museum in New Jersey, for a one of a kind experience. Completed in 1879, the house belonged to a wealthy Philadelphia family, the Physicks. Tour the vast estate normally, experiencing its unique history, or if you are in for a fright, participate in their ghost tours instead. Boo!.

name: Naval Air Station Wildwood Aviation Museum
description: The Naval Air Station (NAS) Wildwood Aviation Museum is located inside a former World War II hangar that dates back to 1943. It has a long history, originally used as a training facility for various aerial missions, then used for incoming and outgoing charter and commuter flights 1990, before it started to break down. Today, the NAS Wildwood Aviation Museum boasts a variety of historic planes, helicopters and WWII memorabilia.

name: World War II Lookout Tower
description: Part of Cape May Point State Park, the World War II Lookout Tower – officially known as Fire Control Tower No. 23 – was built in 1942 and is New Jersey's last restorable tower from World War II. Opened to the public in 2009, the tower played a major role in defending the coast during the war and is part of the Harbor Defense of the Delaware system (known as Fort Miles), which stretched from North Wildwood, New Jersey, to Bethany Beach, Delaware. Today, travelers can climb six flights of stairs to the top of the structure and learn about the historical significance of the area during WWII – as well as how the tower was used to spot enemy ships

name: Cape May Wineries and Vineyards
description: New Jersey is home to more than 50 wineries, and some of the biggest producers can be found in Cape May. Fan favorites include the Cape May Winery and Vineyard and the Willow Creek Winery, but oenophiles should check out all options before picking a spot (though there's no harm in hopping between a few).

name: Congress Hall
description: Along the shoreline of New Jersey's Cape May, you'll find Congress Hall, a historic hotel with boarding house origins dating back to 1816. Today, Congress Hall pays tribute to its past by maintaining much of its Victorian charm – a particular draw for recent guests. The Brown Room, with its Prohibition-era lounge setting, offers nightly entertainment and friendly bartenders that remind visitors of a bygone era.

name: The Virginia Hotel & Cottages
description: Overlooking the New Jersey shoreline from the state's southernmost point, The Virginia Hotel & Cottages in Cape May offers guests a classier alternative to the area's kitschier digs. Guests praise the hotel's efforts to make your trip stress-free, which includes providing complimentary beach chairs, towels and umbrellas for those looking to soak up the sun on the property's private stretch of sand.

name: Ocean City BoardWalk
description: The Ocean City Boardwalk serves as the area's primary pedestrian artery and runs about 2 1/2 miles along the beach. Ocean City's original boardwalk, along with much of the city, burnt down in 1927. The current boardwalk was built immediately after, but sections have been repaired and replaced continuously over time. Currently, the boardwalk hosts amusement park rides, restaurants, stores and more. The Ocean City Boardwalk remains an iconic path to walk, run or bike down.

name: Ocean City Beach
description: The barrier island of Ocean City advertises 8 miles of coast for visitors to explore. The beach's warm weather and strict rules primarily draw visitors looking for a relatively calm and relaxing opportunity to enjoy the saltwater and sun.
address: Ocean City (no address, it is the beach)

name: Corson's Inlet State Park
description: A small strip of undeveloped land, Corson's Inlet State Park was established in 1969 to protect its distinct wildlife. This state park appeals primarily to nature lovers, who want a more organic beach experience than the popular city beach. The park boasts hiking trails that weave through sand dunes and beaches for sun-soaking (but no swimming) and other wilderness areas. There is also a boat launch available for anyone who wants to take advantage of a day on the water.

name: Playland's Castaway Cove
description: More than 32 rides, including a Ferris wheel, make Playland's Castaway Cove stand out on the Ocean City Boardwalk. The amusement park has been operating for more than 60 years and has developed a reputation for its assortment of thrill-seeking and family-friendly rides. In addition to its numerous rides, Playland's Castaway Cove also operates an indoor arcade on-site as well as two mini-golf locations and a go-kart speedway nearby.
price: Ticket Prices vary by rides, games, etc...

name: Gillian's Wonderland Pier
description: An initial iteration of the park opened in 1930 following a fire on the boardwalk, and its primary attractions were a Ferris wheel and a merry-go-round. The park has since moved and expanded to include more than 25 rides, which travelers can ride for a variety of ticket prices. Gillian's Wonderland Pier's attractions skew toward younger children, but there are rides to amuse most ages.
price: Ticket Prices vary by rides, games, etc...

name: Glazed Over Studios
description: Glazed Over Studios offers opportunities to try out pottery, mosaics and canvas walk-in sessions, making it an excellent, impromptu option for Ocean City tourists. Travelers who prefer a more structured learning opportunity can sign up for one of the studio's classes, which are geared toward adults or kids.

name: Stainton's Gallery of Shops
description: Stainton's Gallery of Shops provides space for more than 70 unique vendors to sell their wares. While it's best to shop at Stainton's without expectations, the wares sold can include jewelry, candles, art, pottery, toys and apparel. Past travelers say that Stainton's provides an excellent place to pick up a one-of-a-kind gift or a memorable keepsake.

name: 5 West Pub
description: Pub with calm atmosphere and great food and cocktails. Includes a big screen too

name: SeaSalt Restaurant
description: SeaSalt Restaurant boasts a distinctive fine-dining experience without the fuss: unparalleled beachfront setting, vibrant energy, an impressive menu with something for everyone, along with signature cocktails, a diverse wine list, and truly genuine hospitality.
address: 1035 Beach Avenue, at the Ocean Club Hotel
hours: Open Daily Monday-Sunday until October 21, 8 AM - 9 PM

name: Tisha's
description: Enjoy fine Italian, New-American and Seafood at this restaurant. Patios are available for customers and even pets for an enjoyable experience in the summer months

name: Atlantic Parasail
description: Enjoy parasailing at New Jersey's Originial Parasail Company. Experience the exhilarating thrill of zipping through the sky while peering down at the clear waters of Wildwood
price:
Each parasailor: $82
Observers (not flying): $49
Photo package: $35
Go pro aerial adventure cam: $35
hours: Daily from Memorial Day through Labor Day, 8 AM until sunset

name: Bobby Dee’s Arcade
description: Boasting a wide variety of games, prizes, and merchandise, Bobby Dee's Arcade can serve as an exciting summer experience at WildWood. You can even ask for a special prize!

name: Cape Sea Excursions
description: Star Fleet’s Deep Sea Fishing & Dolphin-Whale Watching Center, serving southern New Jersey’s Cape May, Wildwood and Wildwood Crest with first class deep sea fishing trips and exciting dolphin watching and whale watching tours, and our sunset dinner cruises around Cape May Island. South Jersey is one of the best places on earth to observe wild dolphins! The Starlight Fleet offers a great opportunity for students to explore our oceans, hands-on!

name: Cape Square Entertainment
description: Boasting a movie theatre, bowling alley, golf simulator, arcade, restaurants, bars, the Cape Square Entertainment is an excellent place to view your favorite movies! Afterwards you can grab a quick bite or enjoy bowling and gaming at the various facilities.

name: Doo Wop Museum and Back to the ’50s Neon Night Tours
description: Brimming with cool artifacts, fun memories, fascinating history and bright neon lights, the Doo Wop Experience Museum and Neon Sign Garden is a celebration of architecture, design, music, pop culture and everything else that made Wildwood famous in its heyday of the 1950’s and 1960’s. Tour leaves from the Museum and then by foot, car or guided bus tour view the fun and frivolous origins of postwar 1950’s American in the Wildwoods

name: Morey’s Piers & Beachfront Waterparks
description: Morey’s Piers is a classic seaside amusement park that’s been family owned since 1969. Voted one of the top three seaside amusement parks in the world by Amusement Today, Morey’s Piers has more than 100 rides and attractions spanning 18 acres along six beach blocks and includes three amusement piers and two beachfront water parks.

name: Monster Truck Rides on the Beach
description: The only monster truck ride on the east coast. Come enjoy an unique experience aboard this prowling machine

name: Dark Star Pirate Cruises
description: The Dark Star is an authentic Pirate themed cruise and is looking for Buccaneers young and ol’ to sign on with the crew and ye’ll find a fortune of tales, tunes and treasures. Come sail the 7 seas on this exciting tour!

name: A & LP Foods
description: Stuff yourself with specialty Italian pizza, pasta, steaks, hoagies, and imported products.

name: A Little Cafe
description: A Little Cafe which offers sandwiches, salads, “from scratch” soups and baked goods, along with a full service coffee bar. There also are vegan and gluten free options.

name: 5 Mile Marketplace
description: Shop for a variety of merchandise including beach gear, souvenirs, sundries, swim wear, clothing for the whole family, footwear, jewelry, hermit crabs and more!

name: Beau Boutique
description: A woman’s boutique located on the Wildwoods Boardwalk featuring clothing, jewelry, accessories and much more!
